M-x org-info = manual

spc-m-h (org-toggle-heading)

spc-m-i (org-toggle-item)

tab folds

shift+tab fold all

shift+tab unfolds all level-by-level

g-(j/k) move to element

g-(h/l) next child/parent

C-RET create next heading with same level

M-(h/l) promoto or unpromote

M-(k/j) move whole tree

M-S-(k/j) move only element

To select an element you can use
the org mode text-object "e"

To select a subtree you can use
the org mode text-object "R"

To make a table delimit and surround with |

C-RET next row of table

spc-m-b-\- create new table headline

S-RET duplicate field as next cell

M-(k/j) move row

M-(h/l) move column

M-S-(l/h) expand/delete new column

M-S-(j/k) expand/delete new row

spc-i-s insert snippet

Using TODO as an identifier
causes it to be transitive

RET on a TODO element buries it

spc-m-t toggle generic identifiers

S-*horizontal arrow key* remove/restore
generic identifier

spc-m-d-s org-schedule?

To switch between months in org-schedule use shift-arrow key

To give org-schedule a time just type it

[  ] creates a checkbox

RET check checkbox

RET RET bury checkbox

[%\//] track complete tasks

C-c-[ move to front of agenda

spc-o-a org-agenda

to create a source block use <s

+/- creates an unordered list

numbers create ordered lists

you have to specify the language after the #+BEGIN_SRC

tangle creates a file out of all source code blocks

To use tangle create #+PROPERTY: header-args :tangle *filename*

M-x: org-babel-tangle tangles the org file
